  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>De-link and cut the mini <strong>chorizo</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Cut each <strong>chicken thigh</strong> into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-low&nbsp;heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chorizo</strong> and cook for 1 min, then add the <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 1 min further&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed the <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong>to the pan and continue to cook for approx. 3-4 min</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>olives</strong> roughly</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> boiled water&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add&nbsp;the <strong>rice</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>smoked paprika</strong> to the pan and stir briefly to coat the rice in the oil and spice</p>\r\n<p>Stir&nbsp;in the <strong>stock</strong> and <strong>olives</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and once boiling, reduce the heat to very low, cover with a lid and cook for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Take some time to chill (or wash up!) until the rice is cooked and then move on to the next step&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add half the chopped <strong>parsley</strong> and the juice of half the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> to the pan</p>\r\n<p>Stir gently and taste for seasoning, adding&nbsp;more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/614.-step7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
